{NORTH has a minimum 2\C opening.

SOUTH, with 8 points and a 5-card suit, should make a positive response, 2\S.

NORTH shows the \S support first, to set the trump suit, and to give SOUTH an opportunity 
for a move toward slam if he wants to do so.

SOUTH would now make a Control-showing bid IF HE HAD A CONTROL. Since he doesn't he just returns 
to 4\S which NORTH passes.}

